(Nationair) said it plans to beginservice between Montreal's Mirabel airport and Brussels threetimes a week for an unrestricted one-way fare of 299 Canadiandollars.    The fare will rise to 379 dlrs in high season, beginning June to September, and compares with a regular unrestrictedone-way economy fare of 944 dlrs on Canada's major airlines,Nationair said.    The airlines said it sees the service as an option forbusiness travellers.             Reuter&#3;